com.opera.core.systems

Enum OperaMobileKeys

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<OperaMobileKeys>
      • com.opera.core.systems.OperaMobileKeys
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, CharSequence, Comparable<OperaMobileKeys>

    public enum OperaMobileKeys
extends Enum<OperaMobileKeys>
implements CharSequence
    A soft key is a button flexibly programmable to invoke any of a number of functions rather than being associated with a single fixed function or a fixed set of functions. OperaMobileKeys can be used in combination with WebDriver's Keys for special key input. An example: 
    
   element.sendKeys("foo", OperaMobileKeys.SOFT_KEY_1);
    Since:
    0.19
